  "notes": "Primary source: RFEG club page (federative code LV70), which lists all rated recorridos with per-hole par, hcp, meters, Vc and Vs. Seve Ballesteros design (opened 1998), unusual par-72 layout of 6 par-3s, 6 par-4s, 6 par-5s. Internal consistency verified: pars sum to 72 (36/36), stroke indexes form a permutation of 1-18 (odd SI on front nine, even on back), and every tee's 18 distances sum exactly to the published total (6220/6017/5678/5252/4951 m). Cross-checks: club website hole 1 page shows par 5, hcp 17, 447 m (matches RFEG Amarillas); Golfshake totals in yards convert to RFEG meters (Yellow 6210 yd ~ 5678 m, Red 5414 yd ~ 4951 m; Golfshake's 'White 6820 yd' actually corresponds to the Negras 6220 m tees, a naming discrepancy on Golfshake's side). Same stroke-index allocation applies to all tees per RFEG. Note some third-party sites (golfingholiday/18birdies) carry older imperial data; RFEG values used throughout."
